-- Russia’s Borodin Buys $219 Million U.K. Home, Sunday Times Says
-- B y   E m m a   C h a r l t o n
-- 2012-08-05T10:54:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-05/russia-s-borodin-buys-219-million-u-k-home-sunday-times-says.html
Russian Billionaire Andrei Borodin
paid 140 million pounds ($219 million) for an estate near
Henley-on-Thames in Oxfordshire, U.K., the  Sunday Times  reported
citing a local politician.  The purchase makes the property Britain’s most expensive
house, the newspaper reported. Borodin and his lawyer refused to
comment on the purchase when contacted by the Sunday Times, it
reported, while local councilor John Halsall confirmed the new
owner.  To contact the reporter on this story:
